After following the original README.md, to run CNN compression:
    Frist we train the baseline
    From src/:
        python main.py --class_config 19
    This might take some time but you should be left with:
        baseline.keras- Trained CNN
        X_test.npy, Y_test.npy- preprocessed test data
        X_calib.npy- stratified training samples for int8 calibration
        class_names.npy- readable class names
    Then to compress and benchmark:
        python compress_and_bench.py --model baseline.keras --X_test X_test.npy --y_test y_test.npy --X_calib X_calib.npy --class_names class_names.npy --subsample_test (between 50000 and 200000)
    Output is put in results but also printed neatly in the terminal